    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-12-02T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-12-02T11:00:00-05:00" n="748"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d748">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/12–253: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 748<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Jordan (<persName corresp="#p_MLD1"
                            type="from">Mallory</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d748fn1">Repeated to Paris, London, Baghdad, Beirut, Cairo,
                        Damascus, Jidda, Tel Aviv, and Jerusalem; repeated by the Department to New
                        York.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Amman</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-12-02T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 2, 1953—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1253. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 231.<note n="2" xml:id="d748fn2">
                        <ref target="#d739">Document 739</ref>.</note> Jordan Government today
                    informed Arab diplomatic representatives it proposed reply to invitation UNSYG
                    to conference with Israel as follows:</p>
                <p>Jordan Government will tell SYG proposed meeting impracticable this time. Jordan
                    prepared to discuss with Israel any time within framework mixed armistice
                    commission any amendments desired by Israel or claims she may have or clarify
                    ambiguities. All this can be done, according to Jordan, within framework of
                        <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> under Article II mixed armistice
                    agreement.</p>
                <p>Jordan Government asked immediate comment other Arab Governments on proposed
                    attitude.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Comment:</hi> This tentative decision due intransigence . . .
                    section government led by Foreign Minister Khalidy. Believed decision will be
                    disapproved by many responsible Jordanians including several members cabinet.
                    Decision taken despite repeated strong representations by US and British urging
                    acceptance UNSYG’s invitation. Today UK Ambassador again urged Prime Minister
                    accept and <persName corresp="#p_LAG1">Lynch</persName> again spoke emphatically
                    at Foreign Office.</p>
                <p>Approval by other Arab Leaguers acceptance of invitation might change local
                    attitude but we not assured even this would overcome intransigence and fear.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MLD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mallory</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
